<exercise checkit-seed="0006" checkit-slug="TI6" checkit-title="Partial fractions">
    <statement>
        
        <p>
            Consider the partial fraction decomposition <me> \frac{2 \, {\left(x - 1\right)}}{x^{2} + x}=\frac{4}{x + 1} - \frac{2}{x}.</me>  Use this decomposition to compute <m>\displaystyle\int \frac{2 \, {\left(x - 1\right)}}{x^{2} + x}dx</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <me>\displaystyle\int \frac{2 \, {\left(x - 1\right)}}{x^{2} + x}dx=\displaystyle\int \frac{4}{x + 1} - \frac{2}{x}dx=4 \, \log\left(x + 1\right) - 2 \, \log\left(x\right)+C.</me>
    </answer>
</exercise>
